Mpho Raborife, News24(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Butterworth -&nbsp;A 63-year-old man and his grandson have died after a rondavel they were living caught alight in a village near Centane, Eastern Cape police said on Sunday.An inquest docket was opened after the the man and the 10-year-old boy died in the fire at about 23:00 on Friday night in Qhina village, Captain Jackson Manatha said.The cause of the fire was still unclear.Manatha said four other young boys aged between 10 and 15 managed to escape without sustaining any injuries.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.